KOMPOT USER MANUAL: FILESYSTEM

Kompot is a customised version of the Gentoo distribution of
GNU/Linux. Many files exist throughout the filesystem that change
default configurations and behaviour of Gentoo. Below is the list
of all modified entries outside of "/home". NOTE: portage managed
files not included.


PATHS:

/boot							: Kernel, initramfs, kernel config.

/boot/efi/boot					: Active kernel.

/mnt/usbNUM						: Hotplug USB mount area.

/mnt/hdd						: Hotplug HDD mount area.

/mnt/hdd/Backups/kompot			: Hotplug HDD backup directory.

/opt/bin						: Packages installed without portage.

/opt/vm							: QEMU virtual machine files.

/usr/share/aesthetics			: Term colour values and wallpapers.

/usr/share/vim/vim82/colors		: Kompot vim theme for neovim.

/var/cache/distfiles			: Stores local source packages.

/var/db/manuals					: Location of kompot manual pages.

/var/db/repos/kompot			: Kompot software repository.

/var/db/repos/crossdev			: Crossdev repository.
